dct_description_sm: Relief shown by 10 meter contour interval and spot elevations. Depth shown by fathoms. Shows outlines of buildings (some with names), roads, railways classifeid, boundaries classified, built-up areas, cemetaries, temples, lighthouses, and vegetation by symbols. "For use by War and Navy Department agencies only." Includes glossary, index to boundaries, and coverage diagram. Place names transcribed according to modified Hepburn (Romaji) system.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
